                                 EDITORIAL
     =================================================================


     With this issue, I am resigning as Editor of the FidoNews.

     In the established practice of all FidoNews Editors in Fido history,
     I am urging the International Coordinator to accept the appointment
     of Henk Wolsink as the new FidoNews Editor effective with issue 1533,
     and am asking that the FidoNet Nodelist reflect this change.

     The reasons for my resignation have become obvious to many over the
     last few weeks as an ill-informed effort to force information out by
     coercion and harrassment in various echoes has taken a new and more
     menacing twist.

     In the fine traditions established by their apparent idols and role
     models of Winter and Germer in Zone 1, several have now moved beyond
     the realm of FidoNet and made the distinctive effort to force their
     ways into the private lives of others...even persons who are not a
     part of FidoNet.

     This includes a number of acts, including the distribution of a
     private phone number by persons once trusted; harrassment of a local
     businessman (who has never been involved in FidoNet in any form) by
     the posting of his private business phone; the distribution of a
     description of personal vehicles, as well as license numbers; the
     use of investigators to delve into the privacy of matters outside the
     realm of FidoNet or even myself; and, a credible claim that pictures
     have been taken of the interior of the home of the family that I rent
     from, as well as other less well-documented actions that have been
     observed or reported to me.

     All of this, simply because I hold opinions that are *different* from
     the 'mob mentality' currently engaged in the destruction of Zone 1
     FidoNet in the name of "democracy".

     What protection might have been offered by FidoNet Policy has been
     rendered useless by an administration more interested in how many
     hats someone wears than by what constitutes smooth operations and
     excessively annoying behavior.

     It seems that the idea of the free discussion of ideas in FidoNet has
     been replaced with the concept of the invasion of _personal_ privacy,
     and the posting of personal details that have nothing to do with Fido
     itself...or worse, with those who have nothing to do with whatever
     differences may exist.

     Moreso, the idea seems to be to 'argue the person' and not 'argue the
     idea'...nor are these attitudes directed at myself alone.

     This time, however, innocent bystanders are involved, and because of
     the threats being made, both directly and by inference, I cannot with
     good conscience risk the personal safety or the privacy of my
     landlords and friends beyond this point.
     FIDONEWS 15-32               Page 2                   10 Aug 1998


     Would that I had not had the recent surgery, and were able to move
     into my own residence, things would be different...but that is not
     the case, and I am otherwise helpless to act at this time to protect
     the family who has taken me in.

     But, I can at least let it be known the reasons _why_ I have been
     forced to take these actions.

     The past few issues have carried the title "This edition published
     under duress" for the simple reason that efforts of this sort were
     carried out not to benefit FidoNet, but rather to prevent me from
     posting my own opinions without endangering the privacy of others.

     And a free press is *critical* to any _real_ democracy, regardless
     of the self-serving mouthings by those who have engaged in this
     unprecedented effort to invade personal privacy.

     As a result, and effective with this issue's publication, I will
     withdraw from active participation in FidoNet, save in those echoes
     where I have previous commitments; as well, I will be considering
     my withdrawal from FidoNet altogether, since extortion, witchhunts
     and terrorism seem to be the new 'standard' by which we are being
     allowed to move towards.

     With that, I release the FidoNews to Henk Wolsink, in the hopes that
     a free press will not be smothered or threatened by remaining inside
     of Zone 1 any longer.

     -zf-

