     Obituary = Scott Samet
     by Hector Santos, 1:135/382


     [Editor's Note:  Due to an attempt to hack into my E-Mail account by
     persons as yet unknown, the message originally sent by Andrea Santos
     was lost in the destruction, along with several non-FidoNews articles
     and messages.  With apologies to all involved, I have elected to post
     a copy of Hector Santos' announcement made in several echoes.  -zf-]


     People,

     Scott Samet , the author of one of the more popular FIDONET utilities
     called XLAXNODE.EXE and XLAXDIFF.EXE, has went to the better world.

     As you properly aware in some form or fashion, Scott was one of the
     original Fidonet developers (old address 1:135/990).  His Fidonet
     nodelist compiler was one of the original "hall mark" and "backbone"
     utilities that gave Fidonet one of its early "growth sparks" during
     the 80s.  Nearly every early know Frontend Mailer and/or Mail Echo
     Processor worked with the Nodelist Databases produced by Scott's
     utility.

     I first met Scott in 1984 when I first joined Fidonet. I purchased
     his nodelist compiler for $15.00, like most of the young Fidonet
     members did.  When I started to write Silver Xpress, the first
     Fidonet Offline Mail System, I added support for the compiled
     nodelist and Scott helped by adding support for some my new
     ideas.  Scott added support for the Silver Xpress compiled
     nodelist to XLAXNODE.EXE in subsequent updates.   That fact he
     was an enthusiastic Borland Pascal user and software developer like
     I was, our "Cyber" relationship was even better.  With his expert
     knowledge of Pascal, he helped me add some advance techniques to
     Silver Xpress.

     In October 1987, Scott left Fidonet but thousands of people
     around the globe, till this very day, continued to use his XLAXNODE
     nodelist utilities.

     As an original "hall mark" Fidonet Developer, all members of Fidonet
     deserves the attention of this news. Zorch Forsberg (FidoNews Editor)
     has been contacted, and Andrea Santos (1:3135/382) has informed our
     Net 135 members of the sad news.

     God Bless Scott

     PS: Thank you Borland for posting this information.


                          -------- Forwarded Message ---------
     Original: DATE..... 03 Aug 1998,  12:59p
     Original: FROM..... LORIE HULL <LHULL@INPRISE.COM>
     Original: TO....... ALL
     Original: SUBJECT.. A sad announcement
     Original: FORUM.... borland.public.delphi.non-technical
     FIDONEWS 15-32               Page 11                  10 Aug 1998


     Original: NETWORK.. BORLAND  ECHO: BI_NONTECH

     From: Lorie Hull <lhull@inprise.com>
     Organization: Inprise Corp
     Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

     Scott Samet, a member of TeamB and an active participant in this
     online community, died last week in his home town of Miami, Florida.

     Scott was a member of TeamB for three years. He loved being part of
     TeamB, enjoyed Delphi, and the online community. He loved travel,
     good food, and teaching his nephews about off-color jokes and
     belching. Scott had a finely honed sense of humor, and was always
     ready with a wry remark or pithy comment. Scott was never one to heed
     traditions, social conventions or fashion rules. He had a large and
     diverse group of friends who will miss him greatly, as will his
     family and colleagues.

     Scott was, most definitely, an interesting fellow. I am honored to
     have known him. He will be missed.

     --
     - lorie
